<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B12_3acnx.eps" for="pdf" print-width="200pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
        <subfigure id="idm505721433056">
          <media id="idm505721432928" alt="">
            <image mime-type="" src="../../media/B12_3b.png"/>
<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B12_3b.eps" for="pdf" print-width="200pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
        <subfigure id="idm505721431712">
          <media id="idm505721431584" alt="">
            <image mime-type="" src="../../media/B12_3c.png"/>
<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B12_3c.eps" for="pdf" print-width="200pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
        <subfigure id="idm505721430368">
          <media id="idm505721430240" alt="">
            <image mime-type="" src="../../media/B12_3d.png"/>
<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B12_3d.eps" for="pdf" print-width="200pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
                <subfigure id="idm505721427680">
          <media id="idm505721427552" alt="">
            <image mime-type="" src="../../media/B12_3f.png"/>
<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B12_3f.eps" for="pdf" print-width="200pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
        
      <caption>The output of an LTI system is an infinite sum (an integral) of shifted and scaled versions of the system's impulse response.</caption></figure></section>
    <section id="idm505721411744">
      <title>Properties of Convolution</title>
      <para id="idm505721411200">As with other mathematical operators, convolution also has a variety of properties that will help us out as we start working with it more. Like addition and multiplication, convolution obeys the <emphasis effect="italics">commutative property</emphasis>: </para>
      <para id="idm505721410064">
        <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
          <m:semantics>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>t</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>t</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>t</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
              <m:mi>t</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x_1(t)\ast x_2(t)=x_2(t)\ast x_1(t)</m:annotation>
          </m:semantics>
        </m:math>
      </para>
      <para id="idm505721396560">Proof of this property involves a simple change of variables, letting <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>u</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>τ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">u=t-\tau</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> (meaning also <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>τ</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>u</m:mi></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">\tau=t-u</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>d</m:mi><m:mi>u</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>d</m:mi><m:mi>τ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">du=-d\tau</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>):</para>
      <para id="idm505721386432">
        <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
          <m:semantics>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
              </m:mtable>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:annotation encoding="math/tex">\begin{align*}
x_1(t)\ast x_2(t)&amp;=\int\limits_{\tau=-\infty}^\infty x_1(\tau)x_2(t-\tau)d\tau\\
&amp;=\int\limits_{u=t-(-\infty)}^{t-\infty}x_1(t-u)x_2(u)(-du)\\
&amp;=-\int\limits_{u=\infty}^{-\infty}x_1(t-u)x_2(u)du\\
&amp;=\int\limits_{u=-\infty}^{\infty}x_1(t-u)x_2(u)du\\
&amp;=\int\limits_{u=-\infty}^{\infty}x_2(u)x_1(t-u)du\\
&amp;=x_2(t)\ast x_1(t)
\end{align*}</m:annotation>
          </m:semantics>
        </m:math>
      </para>
      <para xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="idm505721299264">When it comes to the commutative property's relevance to continuous-time LTI systems, what it means is that a signal <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> going through a system with impulse response <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">h(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> will produce the same output as a signal <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">h(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> processed by a system with an impulse response of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> (<link target-id="idm505721285456"/>).</para><figure id="idm505721285456" orient="vertical"><media id="idm505721284688" alt="">
          <image mime-type="" src="../../media/convcommute.png" width="300pt" print-width="250pt"/>
        </media>
        
      <caption>A graphical representation of the commutative property of convolution.</caption></figure><para id="idm505721282816">As with addition and multiplication, convolution also obeys the <emphasis effect="italics">associative property</emphasis>, <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x_1(t)\ast\left(x_2(t)\ast x_3(t)\right)=\left(x_1(t)\ast x_2(t)\right)\ast x_3(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. The proof of this property requires switching the order of integration and using the commutative property a couple times:</para>
      <para id="idm505721259424">
        <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
          <m:semantics>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                    <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                    <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd/>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi/>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
              </m:mtable>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:annotation encoding="math/tex">\begin{align*}
x_1(t)\ast\left(x_2(t)\ast x_3(t)\right)&amp;=x_1(t)\ast(x_3(t)\ast x_2(t))\\
&amp;=\int\limits_{-\infty}^{\infty}x_1(\tau_2)\int\limits_{-\infty}^{\infty}x_3(\tau)x_2((t-\tau_2)-\tau)d\tau ~d\tau_2\\
&amp;=\int\limits_{-\infty}^{\infty}x_3(\tau)\int\limits_{-\infty}^{\infty}x_1(\tau_2)x_2((t-\tau)-\tau_2)d\tau_2 ~d\tau\\
&amp;=x_3(t)\ast(x_1(t)\ast x_2(t))\\
&amp;=\left(x_1(t)\ast x_2(t)\right)\ast x_3(t)
\end{align*}</m:annotation>
          </m:semantics>
        </m:math>
      </para>
      <para id="idm505720417696">The consequence of this property is that two LTI systems in series can be combined to be a single system whose impulse response is the convolution of the individual systems' impulse response (<link target-id="idm505720417248"/>).</para><figure id="idm505720417248" orient="vertical"><media id="idm505720416544" alt="">
          <image mime-type="" src="../../media/convassoc.png" width="400pt" print-width="250pt"/>
        </media>
        
      <caption>A graphical representation of the associative property of convolution.</caption></figure><para id="idm505720414672">Another property, the <emphasis effect="italics">distributive property</emphasis>, can help us to likewise simplify systems in other ways. As with multiplication and addition, the distributive property of convolution is <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x_1(t)\ast(x_2(t)+x_3(t))=x_1(t)\ast x_2(t)+x_1(t)\ast x_3(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. The proof is a matter of splitting a sum within the convolution integral into two separate integrals:</para>
      <para id="idm505720389184">
        <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
          <m:mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              </m:mtd>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mi/>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:munderover>
                  <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                </m:munderover>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd/>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mi/>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:munderover>
                  <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                </m:munderover>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd/>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mi/>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:munderover>
                  <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                </m:munderover>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:munderover>
                  <m:mo>∫</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi>
                </m:munderover>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mi>τ</m:mi>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd/>
              <m:mtd>
                <m:mi/>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>∗</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              </m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
          </m:mtable>
        </m:math>
      </para>
      <para id="idm505720303744">With this property, we can take two LTI systems that are in parallel and combine them into one system with an impulse response that is the sum of the individual systems' impulse responses (<link target-id="idm505720303296"/>).</para><figure id="idm505720303296" orient="vertical"><media id="idm505720302528" alt="">
          <image mime-type="" src="../../media/convdistrib.png" width="400pt" print-width="250pt"/>
        </media>
        
      <caption>A graphical representation of the distributive property of convolution.</caption></figure><para xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="idm505720231936">The final property of convolution, its <emphasis effect="italics">width</emphasis>, has to do with the output that two convolved signals produce. Suppose a signal <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x_1(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is valued at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">0</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> outside a time duration of length <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">T_1</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. Suppose also a signal <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x_2(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is valued at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">0</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> outside a time duration of length <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">T_2</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. The convolved signal <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x_1(t)\ast x_2(t)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> will then be valued at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">0</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> outside a time duration of width <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">T_1+T_2</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> (<link target-id="idm505720202656"/>). We will see why this is the case when we begin to actually compute some convolutions.</para><figure id="idm505720202656" orient="vertical"><subfigure id="idm505720201888">
          <media id="idm505720201760" alt="">
            <image mime-type="" src="../../media/B16_1a.png"/>
<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B16_1a.eps" for="pdf" print-width="250pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
        <subfigure id="idm505720200544">
          <media id="idm505720200416" alt="">
            <image mime-type="" src="../../media/B16_1b.png"/>
<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B16_1b.eps" for="pdf" print-width="250pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
        <subfigure id="idm505720199200">
          <media id="idm505720199072" alt="">
            <image mime-type="" src="../../media/B16_1c.png"/>
<image mime-type="application/postscript" src="../../media/B16_1c.eps" for="pdf" print-width="250pt"/>
          </media>
        </subfigure>
        
      <caption>The width of a convolved signal is the sum of the width of the two signals that were convolved to make it.</caption></figure></section>
